<a name=3D"validate">
<h2>Matching a Person to a Social Security Number</h2>
<p>
</p></a><dir><a name=3D"validate"></a><dir><a name=3D"validate">
Enter the first 3, 5, or 6 digits of a Social Security number (SSN)=20
and select "quick validation" to learn=20
general information about the holder of the SSN.
Enter the full 9 digits of a SSN and select "full validation"
to additionally learn whether the number is likely to be valid.=20
<p>
</p></a><form action=3D"https://dataprivacylab.org/query?htx=3Dfile://ssnx/=
ssn1.htx" method=3D"POST"><a name=3D"validate">
   =20
    <input type=3D"text" size=3D"6" value=3D"" name=3D"enterfirst">
    -
    <input type=3D"text" size=3D"3" value=3D"" name=3D"entermiddle">
    -
    <input type=3D"text" size=3D"9" value=3D"" name=3D"enterlast">
    Example: 078-05-1120 (About this=20
     </a><a href=3D"https://www.ssa.gov/history/ssn/misused.html">SSN</a>)
    <p>
    <select name=3D"entertype">
       <option value=3D"quick">Quick Validation
       </option><option value=3D"full">Full Validation
    </option></select>
    Please allow several seconds for a full validation.
    </p><p>
    <input type=3D"submit" value=3D" Validate SSN ">=20
    <input type=3D"reset" value=3D" Clear ">=20
    &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<a href=3D"https://dataprivacylab.org/dataprivacy/pro=
jects/ssnwatch/samples.html">Sample runs</a>
</p></form>
